A first attempt at a virge driver for XAA. This is a total rewrite, 
so unfortunately there are probably many bugs present and not all features
of the accel virge server are implemented. 


What works: 
- Supports PCI hardware, ViRGE and ViRGE/VX (probably)
- Supports 8bpp, 16bpp and 24bpp. Has not been tested on VX.
  8bpp pixmux on virge seems to work, as do interlace modes.
- VT switching seems to work well, no corruption for 8, 16 and 24bpp. This
  has only been tested on OS/2.
- Acceleration: ScreenToScreen copy, solid rectangle fills, CPU to
  screen color expansion, 8x8 mono and color fills. Currently, this appears
  to be substantially faster than the accel server at least for 
  color expansions. These functions also include planemask support, and there
  is transparency for 8x8 mono fills. Work has started on accelerating lines. 

What does not work for sure:
- No VLB support for now (were there any VLB virge cards produced??)
- None of this doublescan stuff
- The pixmap cache gets corrupted after a VT switch (normal) but XAA still
  uses it. I'm not sure wether the problem is with XAA or higher up. 
- Not all of the XConfig options work as yet, mainly the chipset override.

What probably does not work:
- 16bpp and 24bpp on the VX, as I have no way of testing this. I believe that
  8bpp should work, though.
- Special handling of memory accesses on alpha?
- DGA support
- Many other things which I cannot think of now :-)

What is in the works:
- FIx accelerated lines and polygons.
- Add ImageWrite, also maybe use PCI DMA when doing fills.

- Fixing the bugs :-)

XCONFIG options:
- "pci_burst_off" will disable the PCI busrt mode
- "slow_edodram" will switch the ViRGE to 2-cycle edo mode
- "fpm_vram" will switch the ViRGE/VX to fast page mode vram mode
- "fast_dram" increases the mclk value. This is still not finalized.
- "noaccel" turns off all acceleration
- "set_memclk value" sets the video memory clock rate to 'value' (in MHz)

Sebastien Marineau 
04/04/97




